# Public site URL for SEO metadata, sitemap, and robots (no trailing slash).
# Prefer full URL with https://. A bare hostname (e.g. catalog.example.org) is accepted and normalized to https://.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.example

# Same origin as the app (Payload admin + APIs). No trailing slash.
# Production / Vercel: your live URL. Local dev: use http://localhost:3000 (not the prod URL).
# If you use a custom domain (e.g. https://catalog.flossk.org), do **not** leave this as *.vercel.app
# unless that is what users actually open — Payload resolves serverURL from SITE before SERVER.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Payload `serverURL` in **development** ignores NEXT_PUBLIC_* and defaults to http://localhost:PORT
# so copied production .env does not break admin auth. Set only if you use a tunnel:
# PAYLOAD_SERVER_URL=https://your-tunnel.example
# Production (Vercel): set PAYLOAD_SERVER_URL=https://your-canonical-domain (no trailing slash) so admin
# cookies/CSRF match the custom domain even if NEXT_PUBLIC_* was baked into an older build.
# Bare hostnames (e.g. catalog.example.org) are normalized to https:// for Payload serverURL.
# Optional: PAYLOAD_CSRF_EXTRA_ORIGINS=https://www.your-domain.example (comma-separated) if you use www + apex.
#   Production POST /api/suggest-tool: when the browser sends Origin, it must match Host (or X-Forwarded-Host) or a
#   hostname from NEXT_PUBLIC_* / PAYLOAD_SERVER_URL / VERCEL_* / this comma list.

# Payload — generate a long random string in production
PAYLOAD_SECRET=replace-with-long-random-secret

# SQLite — local file (default) or remote libSQL (required on Vercel + /admin)
# Local:
# DATABASE_URL=file:./data/payload.sqlite
#
# Turso (recommended names per https://docs.turso.tech/integrations/vercel ):
# TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://your-db-name-yourorg.turso.io
# TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=eyJ...
# Alternative names (also supported):
# DATABASE_URL=libsql://...
# DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN=eyJ...
# Use one pair only. Do not wrap values in quotes in the Vercel UI. Enable Production (and Preview if needed).
#
# If /admin or `npm run payload:migrate:status` fails with "Failed query" or HTTP 401 in the server log,
# the Turso auth token is missing, wrong, or expired. In the Turso dashboard, open the database →
# "Create token" (or rotate), then set DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN / TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN in .env and Vercel.
#
# Local-only SQLite (no Turso): comment out DATABASE_URL and DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN so Payload uses the
# default file at data/payload.sqlite (see payload.config.ts), then run: npm run payload:migrate
#
# Postgres (e.g. Supabase):
# — Vercel / GitHub Actions / Render: outbound DB is IPv4-only. Supabase “Direct” uses db.*.supabase.co (IPv6).
#   Use Supavisor “Session pooler” from Supabase Connect (host aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com, port 5432).
#   See https://supabase.com/docs/guides/platform/ipv4-address
# — Transaction mode (port 6543) can break Drizzle/Payload prepared statements; prefer Session pooler :5432.
# TLS: do not copy `VERCEL=1` alone into local .env (use `VERCEL=1` + `VERCEL_URL` only on Vercel) — affects URI sslmode.
#   Supabase: pg pool uses relaxed Node TLS by default (`rejectUnauthorized: false`); URI sslmode defaults to
#   require+uselibpqcompat (verify-full only with PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_TLS_STRICT=1 on real Vercel). TLS_STRICT may cause
#   SELF_SIGNED_CERT on some networks; leave unset for the default relaxed chain.
#   Override sslmode: PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_SSLMODE=verify-full|require|disable
#   If you see "self-signed certificate in certificate chain" locally: try unsetting PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_TLS_STRICT, or
#   PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_TLS_INSECURE=1 (dev only). Non-Supabase Postgres: PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_TLS_INSECURE=1 (temporary / dev).
# PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_POOL_MAX=2
# Optional: pg pool `max` (default **1** whenever `VERCEL=1`, 15 locally). Values **>2** on Vercel are clamped to **1**.
# Supabase session `pool_size` is global — many lambdas × high max → “could not reach database” / admin failures.
# PAYLOAD_POSTGRES_PUSH=false
# Leave false in production. Set true only for an intentional one-time schema push on Postgres.
#
# Vercel Blob — Payload `media` uploads on Vercel (removes “storage adapter” warning). Optional locally (uses `staticDir`).
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=vercel_blob_rw_...
# Vercel → Storage → **Create Database** → **Blob** (not Postgres) → link to this project; token is usually injected as `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN`.
# Must match `vercel_blob_rw_<alnum>_<alnum>`; a bad value is skipped at startup so /admin still loads (fix token to enable Blob).
# `payload.config` uses `clientUploads: true` so uploads bypass Vercel’s small server upload limit (see storage-vercel-blob README).

# Draft preview: same value used in /api/draft?secret=
PREVIEW_SECRET=replace-with-preview-secret

# Optional: “From” for Payload console email adapter (password reset, etc. are logged, not sent until you add e.g. Resend/Nodemailer)
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com
# SMTP_FROM_NAME=OpenCatalog

# Force static seed data (skip CMS reads)
# USE_STATIC_CATALOG=false

# When CMS has zero tools, fall back to static data (default true). Set false to show empty.
# CMS_FALLBACK_STATIC=true

# When CMS has tools, merge in static `data/tools.ts` (SourceForge + opensource seeds, etc.).
# CMS entries override the same slug. Set false for a CMS-only catalog.
# CMS_MERGE_STATIC_TOOLS=true

# Visitor “Suggest FOSS” form: comma-separated admin inboxes for email notifications (defaults to all admin users)
# TOOL_SUGGESTION_NOTIFY_EMAIL=you@example.com,other@example.com
#
# Cloudflare Turnstile — https://developers.cloudflare.com/turnstile/
# Local / Preview: test keys (always pass) or your widget keys:
NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=1x00000000000000000000AA
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
#
# Production (Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables → **Production** only):
# Create a Turnstile widget, then set the *production* pair (override test keys on live deploys):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY_PRODUCTION=0x4AAAAAA...
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY_PRODUCTION=0x4AAAAAA...
# If unset in production, the suggest form shows no widget (empty site key). Use the site key and secret from the *same* Turnstile widget; mismatched pairs always fail server verification.

# After creating `.env`, run once: npm run seed:catalog (loads this file via Node --env-file)
# Optional: first admin for `npm run seed:catalog`
# SEED_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@example.com
# SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD=changeme
